# Design System & UI Principles

## Apple Human Interface Guidelines (HIG)

### Typography
- **Font Family**: SF Pro (Text/Display variants)
- **Line Height**: Optimized for readability across all text sizes
- **Letter Spacing**: Carefully tuned for legibility
- **Responsive Typography**: Scales appropriately across device sizes

### Layout & Spacing
- **Grid System**: 4/8px base grid system
- **Key Margins**: 16px, 20px, 24px for component hierarchy
- **Consistent Spacing**: All components follow the same spacing patterns
- **Responsive Layout**: Adapts gracefully to different screen sizes

### Colors
- **Role-based Colors**: Accent, Label, Background, Fill color roles
- **Light/Dark Mode**: Full support for both themes
- **Accessibility**: WCAG 2.2 AA+ contrast compliance
- **System Preferences**: Respects "Increase Contrast" and "Reduce Transparency"

### Interactive Elements
- **Minimum Tap Areas**: 44Ã—44px minimum for all interactive elements
- **Touch-friendly**: All UI elements sized appropriately for touch interaction
- **Keyboard Navigation**: Full keyboard accessibility support
- **Screen Reader**: Complete screen reader compatibility

### Motion & Animation
- **Meaningful Transitions**: Only use motion that serves a purpose
- **Reduced Motion**: Provide static alternatives when `prefers-reduced-motion` is enabled
- **Smooth Animations**: 60fps animations with proper easing curves
- **Performance**: Hardware-accelerated animations only

### Visual Hierarchy
- **Corner Radius**: Applied by element hierarchy (4px, 8px, 12px, 20px)
- **Elevation**: Clear visual separation between layers
- **Focus States**: Clear indication of keyboard focus
- **Loading States**: Informative feedback during async operations

## Component Design Principles

### Consistency
- **Design Tokens**: Centralized token system for colors, spacing, typography
- **Component Library**: Reusable components with consistent behavior
- **Pattern Library**: Established patterns for common UI scenarios

### Accessibility First
- **WCAG 2.2 AA+**: All components meet or exceed accessibility standards
- **Color Independence**: Information not conveyed by color alone
- **Motor Accessibility**: Works with switch control and other assistive technologies
- **Cognitive Accessibility**: Clear, simple, and predictable interactions

